01:14.874 --> 01:16.899
You still love me, don't you?

01:19.846 --> 01:22.041
I have to go see Lindsey.

01:26.653 --> 01:27.711
<i>(GIVE</i> MYHEARTPLAYING)

01:27.821 --> 01:31.757
<i>The water is rushing in</i>

01:32.492 --> 01:36.656
<i>I feel it on my skin</i>

01:36.996 --> 01:42.935
<i>Our boat is sinking now</i>

01:46.873 --> 01:48.272
<i>I wake up</i>

01:48.341 --> 01:49.638
Lindsey?

01:50.810 --> 01:52.937
I'm gonna go to New York, Lucas.

01:54.080 --> 01:56.071
I'm not sure when I'll be back.

01:57.350 --> 02:00.478
Don't do this. I know you're upset, I know.

02:00.553 --> 02:05.456
But you need to believe me
when I tell you, you're the girl I love.

02:05.592 --> 02:07.685
<i>What's the point of it all?</i>

02:09.195 --> 02:11.390
Then how come you never gave me this?

02:17.003 --> 02:19.494
I got home and I thought I'd do
some menial chore,

02:19.572 --> 02:22.040
to get my mind off of how angry I was.

02:23.209 --> 02:25.837
Laundry was the first thing
that came to mind.

02:27.747 --> 02:28.907
(SIGHING)

02:31.117 --> 02:33.881
Who hides a ring in a sock drawer, Luke?

02:33.953 --> 02:36.854
- Lindsey, that ring...
- Don't. I'm just gonna go.

02:37.090 --> 02:40.218
<i>Give me heart</i>
<i>Just give me hope</i>

02:41.361 --> 02:43.056
<i>Give me love</i>

02:43.129 --> 02:45.029
For the record,

02:46.866 --> 02:51.132
it's as beautiful as I imagined it would be.

02:53.206 --> 02:55.197
<i>Give me something</i>

02:55.275 --> 02:56.867
Take it.

02:58.578 --> 03:02.742
I was waiting to give you the ring until
I was sure I had another book in me.

03:04.017 --> 03:08.283
I just don't want you to end up
regretting me because I can't finish.

03:10.123 --> 03:11.920
I would never regret you.

03:11.991 --> 03:13.151
You say that now.

03:14.794 --> 03:17.262
But what if I'm not Lucas the writer?
What if I'm

03:17.330 --> 03:19.821
Lucas the small-time basketball coach?

03:20.633 --> 03:22.658
What if that's all I'm ever gonna be?

03:23.002 --> 03:26.403
<i>And the ocean</i>
<i>is not a home</i>

03:26.472 --> 03:29.703
Then I'd be the small-town
basketball coach's wife.

03:30.543 --> 03:31.874
<i>All alone</i>

03:31.945 --> 03:33.913
Look at me, Lucas.

03:35.148 --> 03:37.343
I don't love you for your book.

03:39.219 --> 03:42.245
I love you for the mind
that book sprang from.

03:43.022 --> 03:46.458
And I don't care if you
never write another word again.

03:50.296 --> 03:55.290
You will always be more than
a small-town basketball coach.

03:59.539 --> 04:01.973
Because you'll be the man that I love.

04:12.518 --> 04:14.713
Lindsey

04:17.824 --> 04:20.224
Evelyn Strauss.

04:22.862 --> 04:24.693
Will you marry me?

04:30.737 --> 04:33.137
(SIGHING)

04:39.746 --> 04:41.043
(LAUGHING)

04:41.114 --> 04:44.572
<i>All I ever really wanted was to</i>

04:45.018 --> 04:49.580
<i>All I ever really wanted was to</i>

04:49.889 --> 04:54.417
<i>All I ever really wanted was to</i>

04:54.694 --> 04:57.458
<i>Dream</i>

04:58.598 --> 05:02.534
Lindsey. I'm sorry. I never wanted...

05:02.602 --> 05:04.832
Lucas asked me to marry him.

05:05.571 --> 05:09.564
<i>Give me love</i>
<i>Just give me warmth</i>

05:10.343 --> 05:14.541
<i>Give me all I never knew</i>

05:17.183 --> 05:18.514
<i>Give me something</i>

05:18.584 --> 05:20.814
(SNIFFS)

05:24.691 --> 05:25.885
Are you awake?

05:27.760 --> 05:29.091
No.

05:34.167 --> 05:35.964
Sorry I got upset with you.

05:37.437 --> 05:39.337
You were right to be upset.

05:40.640 --> 05:44.974
I finally started walking again. I've got
no business being in some guy's face.

05:46.012 --> 05:47.639
<i>Give me something</i>

05:47.714 --> 05:49.705
(SIGHING)

05:51.084 --> 05:52.847
Lucas kissed Peyton.

05:54.454 --> 05:56.979
What? When?

05:58.091 --> 06:00.457
Before we left Tric, in Peyton's office.

06:01.060 --> 06:04.962
I walked in and I saw the whole thing,
or enough of it.

06:05.031 --> 06:06.293
(GRUNTS)

06:08.201 --> 06:10.499
I don't understand how Lucas
can do this to Lindsey,

06:10.570 --> 06:12.629
after everything that
they've been through.

06:12.705 --> 06:14.866
And Peyton, who...
Who does she think she is?

06:14.941 --> 06:17.501
She turned down Lucas' proposal,
she broke his heart.

06:17.577 --> 06:20.068
She has no right to take him from Lindsey.

06:20.146 --> 06:22.341
Maybe it wasn't what it looked like.

06:22.548 --> 06:26.382
Maybe it was just a friendly kiss
or maybe it was a good-bye kiss.

06:26.452 --> 06:28.579
Maybe it was just a mistake.

06:28.654 --> 06:30.645
No, I know what I saw.

06:30.723 --> 06:34.853
This was a full-on,
romantic Lucas/Peyton kiss.

06:36.329 --> 06:38.524
Then you should forget what you saw.

06:38.598 --> 06:40.793
Oh, really? Forget it?

06:41.968 --> 06:44.562
How...
No, what I need to do is tell Lindsey.

06:44.637 --> 06:46.468
Now, see, that's not your place.

06:46.539 --> 06:50.908
Regardless of what it looked like.
I mean, look, if Lucas

06:50.977 --> 06:55.038
is cheating on Lindsey, then he needs to
be man enough to tell her himself.

07:06.192 --> 07:10.094
You know, of all the guys I dated
in New York, not one of them

07:10.163 --> 07:12.495
ever named a shot after me.

07:12.565 --> 07:14.533
I think it kind of separates you

07:14.600 --> 07:19.560
from all the rich, handsome, famous,
successful, educated types.

07:20.306 --> 07:23.036
Flatter me all you want, you're still cut off.

07:23.109 --> 07:26.601
Listen, pal, my name
is technically a brand.

07:26.679 --> 07:30.672
So I could sue you
for naming that shot after me.

07:30.917 --> 07:33.647
First of all, you named the shot
after yourself.

07:34.220 --> 07:37.189
Second of all, that shot was named
the Patricia Foster last week,

07:37.256 --> 07:38.917
the Liz Thompson the week before,

07:38.991 --> 07:41.118
chances are it'll have a new name
tomorrow night,

07:41.194 --> 07:44.254
so if you wanna sue me, better do it fast.

07:45.631 --> 07:49.431
Well, if my name's only gonna be on it
for the night,

07:49.502 --> 07:51.993
maybe there's something else
I should do real fast.

07:53.172 --> 07:56.505
I think you are way too full of yourself
to make that kind of decision.

07:56.576 --> 07:57.565
I...

07:57.677 --> 07:59.372
(BEEPING)

07:59.445 --> 08:01.037
Hi, P. Sawyer.

08:02.515 --> 08:04.983
Please tell me those are tears of joy.

08:05.885 --> 08:08.115
Okay, no, I'm coming home right now.

08:08.187 --> 08:11.782
Oh, not so fast, headline waiting to
happen, I'll drop you off.

08:12.458 --> 08:13.652
You do like me.

08:13.726 --> 08:18.129
No, you driving drunk is just something
I actually can get sued for.

08:30.810 --> 08:32.903
(DIALING CELL PHONE)

08:35.414 --> 08:37.279
<i>It's Millicent, leave a message.</i>

08:37.350 --> 08:41.342
Hi, Millicent, it's... It's Mouth. Marvin.

08:41.419 --> 08:44.878
Mouth. I just wanted you to know
I had a really nice time with you tonight,

08:44.957 --> 08:48.188
and I'm sorry if it ended weird
or if you felt bad.

08:48.327 --> 08:50.795
Not that you should feel bad,
I should feel bad.

08:50.863 --> 08:52.990
I do feel bad.

08:53.065 --> 08:55.158
So call me.

08:55.234 --> 08:56.929
Marvin. Mouth.

08:57.904 --> 08:59.872
I mean, you should call me
and my name is Marvin or Mouth.

08:59.939 --> 09:01.600
Not you should call me Marvin.
I just want...

09:01.674 --> 09:02.663
<i>(MACHINE BEEPS)</i>

09:03.342 --> 09:04.809
(SIGHS)

09:05.444 --> 09:06.968
<i>(BRIGHTRED STAR</i> PLAYING)

09:09.415 --> 09:10.848
(DOOR OPENING)

09:10.917 --> 09:14.785
<i>Mary is my bright red star</i>

09:14.854 --> 09:17.982
Tell me you are not
lying here torturing yourself

09:18.057 --> 09:20.548
with a copy of Lucas' book.

09:21.260 --> 09:24.787
"At that moment my triumph
was not a state championship,

09:25.865 --> 09:29.062
"but a moment of clarity."

09:29.835 --> 09:33.293
<i>And then she'd call me up</i>
<i>Just to wake me up</i>

09:33.372 --> 09:36.068
I've read it, honey, I know how it ends.

09:37.810 --> 09:40.438
It's funny.

09:40.513 --> 09:43.311
Because it seems like Lucas has forgotten.

09:45.217 --> 09:48.050
(SOBBING)
Brooke, he asked Lindsey to marry him.

09:48.721 --> 09:51.155
What? That's crazy.

09:51.524 --> 09:54.687
Maybe, or maybe
crazy is me thinking that...

09:54.760 --> 09:57.957
That he could still have feelings for me
after all these years.

09:59.065 --> 10:02.466
We both know Lucas has a history of

10:02.535 --> 10:04.628
throwing himself
into the wrong relationship,

10:04.704 --> 10:08.162
especially when he can't
admit the truth about who he loves.

10:09.742 --> 10:10.731
No.

10:11.477 --> 10:12.842
It's different this time.

10:13.546 --> 10:15.605
<i>She wears a hat in the sun, pink nails</i>

10:15.681 --> 10:16.875
Okay.

10:16.949 --> 10:19.509
<i>And her bleach blond locks</i>

10:20.553 --> 10:22.350
What am I supposed to do?

10:24.690 --> 10:28.251
<i>So we could meet up</i>

10:28.594 --> 10:29.993
<i>But she's alright</i>

10:30.062 --> 10:31.393
Come here.

10:37.103 --> 10:40.561
<i>She's alright</i>

10:40.640 --> 10:42.767
First, you're gonna let go.

10:45.578 --> 10:50.515
<i>Mary is my bright red star</i>

10:52.852 --> 10:55.343
<i>We just talk into the night</i>
<i>about nothing in particular</i>

10:55.421 --> 10:56.979
Now we're gonna sit.

10:58.557 --> 11:00.457
And you are gonna cry on my shoulder,

11:00.526 --> 11:03.427
for as long as you need to. Okay?

11:03.896 --> 11:05.523
(SIGHING)

11:05.598 --> 11:06.724
Come here.

11:08.100 --> 11:11.263
<i>LUKE: Suddenly, it was as if</i>
<i>the roar of the crowd,</i>

11:11.337 --> 11:14.568
<i>the echo of the final buzzer,</i>
<i>the cheers of my teammates</i>

11:14.640 --> 11:17.768
<i>were all sounding</i>
<i>from a thousand miles away.</i>

11:21.647 --> 11:26.380
<i>And what remained in that bizarre,</i>
<i>muffled silence was only Peyton,</i>

11:26.452 --> 11:29.910
<i>the girl whose art and passion</i>
<i>and beauty had changed my life.</i>

11:32.425 --> 11:34.222
<i>She's alright</i>

11:34.293 --> 11:38.457
<i>In that moment, my triumph</i>
<i>was not a state championship,</i>

11:38.531 --> 11:40.362
<i>but simple clarity.</i>

11:40.433 --> 11:42.765
<i>The realization that we had always</i>
<i>been meant for each other</i>

11:42.835 --> 11:45.770
<i>and every instinct to the contrary</i>
<i>had simply been a denial</i>

11:45.838 --> 11:47.567
<i>of the following truth...</i>

11:54.146 --> 11:57.343
<i>I was now, and would always be,</i>

11:57.416 --> 11:59.748
<i>in love with Peyton Sawyer.</i>

12:14.333 --> 12:16.233
HALEY: Hi, I'm really sorry we're late.

12:16.335 --> 12:19.065
Hey, no TV for you and no ice cream
until the afternoon.

12:19.138 --> 12:20.935
Keep it to one scoop, okay?

12:22.007 --> 12:23.668
One, okay.

12:24.777 --> 12:26.005
You forgot.

12:26.078 --> 12:28.945
It's fine, okay. You look so handsome.

12:29.014 --> 12:33.576
Okay, your dad's gonna pick you up
after practice, all right? Bye.

12:34.620 --> 12:36.281
- Thank you.
- Bye.

12:36.822 --> 12:38.585
- Haley. I'm so glad you're here.
- Hi.

12:38.657 --> 12:41.717
Oh, I gotta go, actually,
but is everything okay?

12:41.794 --> 12:42.954
Oh, everything's great.

12:43.028 --> 12:46.862
I mean as long as this town's
big enough for two Mrs. Scotts.

12:48.300 --> 12:50.564
Oh, my God.

12:52.772 --> 12:53.932
Uh...

12:55.341 --> 12:58.105
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

13:02.481 --> 13:03.675
Hangover?

13:03.783 --> 13:05.944
More like teetering on the edge of death.

13:06.018 --> 13:07.042
(SIGHS)

13:07.119 --> 13:08.347
(SIGHS)

13:10.923 --> 13:13.153
Don't you need that?

13:13.225 --> 13:15.022
I'll brew more.

13:15.561 --> 13:16.619
Thanks.

13:16.762 --> 13:19.731
Listen, I don't remember
much of last night.

13:19.799 --> 13:22.791
But I have a feeling I was
less than professional.

13:24.403 --> 13:27.429
Well, it's probably my fault
for not cutting you off.

13:27.506 --> 13:29.667
But, hey, on the bright side,
at least your drunken mistake

13:29.742 --> 13:31.903
didn't ruin your basketball career.

13:32.711 --> 13:34.542
Did it ruin my nanny career?

13:35.748 --> 13:38.012
You gotta stop the flirting, Carrie.

13:38.083 --> 13:39.243
And the skinny-dipping and...

13:39.318 --> 13:44.085
I think the severity of this hangover pretty
much guarantees it'll never happen again.

13:44.557 --> 13:46.047
I hope that's true.

13:47.193 --> 13:49.218
Drink plenty of water.

14:00.439 --> 14:02.634
Hey, Mouth, did... What are you doing?

14:02.708 --> 14:05.905
- Well, the thing is, I...
- Did you hear about Alice?

14:05.978 --> 14:07.377
She got fired.

14:07.446 --> 14:09.346
What? When?

14:09.415 --> 14:11.508
First thing this morning.
She's already gone.

14:11.584 --> 14:12.983
How great is that?

14:13.052 --> 14:15.350
That is greater than you know.

14:15.454 --> 14:18.321
So what happened? You think they found
out about how abusive she was, or...

14:18.390 --> 14:21.917
Not exactly. Apparently
she was sleeping with an employee.

14:21.994 --> 14:24.292
They're totally, like, cleaning house.

14:39.812 --> 14:42.542
Man, we ain't gonna never beat La Salle
if you gonna be late.

14:42.615 --> 14:45.584
Actually, we're never gonna beat La Salle,
even if you're on time.

14:45.651 --> 14:48.347
Well, maybe I should've spent last night
planning a strategy to win,

14:48.420 --> 14:50.388
instead of getting engaged, huh?

14:50.456 --> 14:51.718
Definitely.

14:52.992 --> 14:55.460
Wait, hold on.
Did you just say, "Engaged"?

14:55.527 --> 14:56.585
(CHUCKLING)

14:56.662 --> 14:59.460
Congratulations, big brother,
that's awesome.

14:59.531 --> 15:01.396
No doubt, baby. Way to go.

15:02.268 --> 15:04.259
So who's the lucky girl?

15:04.770 --> 15:06.635
- You're kidding, right?
- No, that's a legit question.

15:06.705 --> 15:09.299
I mean, we figure with Peyton back
in town, it could be anybody's ballgame.

15:09.375 --> 15:11.866
- Could even be Brooke by now, right?
- Stop.

15:12.311 --> 15:13.835
It's Lindsey.

15:13.913 --> 15:15.175
Excellent choice.

15:15.247 --> 15:17.579
Looks like things might work out
for you after all.

15:17.816 --> 15:18.805
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

15:22.354 --> 15:23.878
Maybe not.

15:25.557 --> 15:29.220
You see what I'm talking about?
You can't just hit people.

15:29.295 --> 15:31.889
Man, all I know is Mrs. James Scott
needed somebody to defend her honor,

15:31.964 --> 15:33.898
and her own husband wasn't
man enough to do it.

15:33.966 --> 15:35.263
Let me tell you something.

15:35.334 --> 15:37.427
My wife's honor is not something
that can be taken away

15:37.503 --> 15:39.630
by some loudmouth jackass in a bar.

15:40.739 --> 15:43.230
What can be taken away
is your ability to play.

15:43.309 --> 15:44.970
It looks like it's just a sprain.

15:45.044 --> 15:47.239
Could be a few days, could be a month.

15:47.313 --> 15:50.441
That's just great.
That's a hell of a punch, Q.

15:50.516 --> 15:52.507
You might have taken out
a whole team with it.

16:00.726 --> 16:01.920
Hi.

16:02.494 --> 16:06.123
If you wanted to break my heart,
there are a thousand ways you could do it.

16:07.166 --> 16:10.727
You did not have to
propose to Lindsey to hurt me.

16:12.905 --> 16:15.203
It didn't have anything to do with you.

16:16.075 --> 16:18.236
It was just weird timing.

16:19.144 --> 16:22.113
Weird timing. Okay, Luke.

16:24.516 --> 16:28.213
- I know that it must seem like...
- No, don't marry her, Luke!

16:29.121 --> 16:31.715
- Peyton, you can't...
- Am I crazy?

16:32.858 --> 16:34.553
Do you not feel what I have felt

16:34.626 --> 16:36.651
every day that we've been apart
for the last three years?

16:36.729 --> 16:42.099
Because I have felt there is this vital piece
of me that's been missing.

16:42.568 --> 16:43.694
And I tried to fill it, Luke.

16:43.769 --> 16:48.570
I tried to fill it with work
and friends and music.

16:49.108 --> 16:52.509
And it stayed empty until last night
when you kissed me,

16:52.745 --> 16:55.908
and my entire universe
snapped back into focus.

16:57.916 --> 17:00.009
Lucas, look me in the eye

17:00.085 --> 17:01.416
and tell me that that kiss did not feel

17:01.487 --> 17:04.285
exactly the same as it felt three years ago.

17:08.627 --> 17:10.288
I'm in love with her, Peyton.

17:15.233 --> 17:16.861
What is going on here?

17:18.069 --> 17:21.597
Just congratulating Luke.

17:22.273 --> 17:23.866
Did you hear he's engaged?

17:24.009 --> 17:26.772
Yeah, I'm gonna be her matron of honor.

17:33.118 --> 17:35.678
Luke, I need to talk to you alone.

17:55.240 --> 17:57.208
Something you want to tell me?

17:58.777 --> 18:00.108
Is this a trick question?

18:00.179 --> 18:03.637
Luke, marriage is a huge commitment.

18:03.715 --> 18:06.843
Can you honestly tell me
that you're positive Lindsey's the one?

18:06.919 --> 18:09.979
Okay, I know where this is going.
Tell you the truth...

18:10.422 --> 18:12.652
Lindsey will always be my number two.

18:14.026 --> 18:17.621
But only because you are my number one.

18:17.696 --> 18:19.391
And you always will be.
Just don't tell Lindsey or Nathan.

18:19.465 --> 18:22.195
Lucas, marriage is serious, and you better
be ready to commit to Lindsey

18:22.267 --> 18:23.859
for the rest of your life.

18:27.372 --> 18:29.533
Does that mean you're happy for me?

18:29.975 --> 18:33.934
<i>WOMAN ON TV:</i>
<i>Get the doctor! Get the doctor! Nurse.</i>

18:34.146 --> 18:35.875
Mama said no TV.

18:35.948 --> 18:36.972
<i>NURSE ON TV: She's at 125 over 70.</i>

18:37.049 --> 18:39.347
Shh. What mama doesn't know
won't hurt her.

18:39.418 --> 18:43.377
<i>NURSE ON TV: She's okay. We've set</i>
<i>the monitor to notify of any changes.</i>

18:45.023 --> 18:47.514
Let me know if Adrian tells Lexine
they harvested the wrong lung.

18:47.593 --> 18:49.322
You know he's going to.

18:53.599 --> 18:55.260
Can I help you?

18:55.334 --> 18:57.234
Looking for a gift for this girl I know.

18:57.302 --> 18:59.770
Well, you've definitely
come to the right place.

18:59.838 --> 19:01.738
What's this girl look like?

19:01.807 --> 19:03.866
Dark hair, hazel eyes.

19:06.712 --> 19:10.614
If she didn't already own it,
I bet she'd like this one.

19:11.550 --> 19:15.919
Yeah, but she's a little taller than you,
so, you have any other sizes?

19:15.988 --> 19:17.751
Brooke, it's Victoria.

19:17.823 --> 19:20.519
She's setting a meeting for you
with a furrier.

19:21.860 --> 19:23.589
One sec.

19:24.963 --> 19:27.523
Apparently, furs are about to make
an unprecedented comeback.

19:27.599 --> 19:29.590
Really? Jamie, cover your ears.

19:30.536 --> 19:32.766
Hi, let's make this short and sweet.

19:32.838 --> 19:37.207
There is no situation in which I am
going to kill furry woodland creatures

19:37.276 --> 19:40.473
to make coats out of them, okay? Thanks.

19:43.348 --> 19:46.442
Let me guess.
Bar hag's still calling the shots?

19:47.519 --> 19:50.784
Aren't you supposed to be shopping
for some fugly giantess?

19:51.056 --> 19:54.787
I'm just saying, why do you work with her
if she makes you that crazy?

19:54.927 --> 19:58.658
Well, first of all, the bar hag,
as you call her, is my mother.

19:58.730 --> 20:01.426
And second of all,
she's my business partner.

20:01.500 --> 20:04.094
And if it weren't for her, I wouldn't have
a bazillion-dollar company,

20:04.169 --> 20:06.660
a magazine and all these lovely clothes
you see here.

20:07.606 --> 20:11.440
My mother wanted me to be
an orthodontist, but I just said no.

20:11.877 --> 20:15.108
Judging from your car,
maybe you should have reconsidered.

20:16.081 --> 20:17.912
Jab against my car.

20:18.483 --> 20:20.041
You're that girl, huh?

20:22.921 --> 20:24.616
That's disappointing.

20:31.129 --> 20:33.962
What's underneath all the clothes,
Brooke Davis?

20:43.842 --> 20:48.074
Hey, Peyton, it's me, Molly.
I live in your old bedroom...

20:48.146 --> 20:50.774
Right, right, keeper of my closet door, hey.

20:50.849 --> 20:53.477
If I'd known other people would be reading
everything I wrote on that thing,

20:53.552 --> 20:55.042
I probably would have been more careful.

20:55.120 --> 20:56.678
Well, I'm glad you weren't.

20:56.755 --> 21:01.215
I wanted to ask, did Lucas really carry you
out of the library after you got shot?

21:01.627 --> 21:03.561
Yeah.

21:03.795 --> 21:05.228
That must have been so romantic.

21:05.297 --> 21:09.324
Well, I was actually kind of preoccupied,
bleeding out on the library carpet, so...

21:09.401 --> 21:11.198
Didn't really think about that.

21:11.270 --> 21:14.933
I don't really remember writing
that part down on my closet doors.

21:18.443 --> 21:22.311
- Oh, right. Of course.
- I've read it 13 times. Is that weird?

21:22.381 --> 21:24.747
Well, it's just that,
when we moved into our new house

21:24.816 --> 21:27.512
and I read your closet door,
I knew it was special.

21:27.586 --> 21:29.451
Then I read this book.

21:29.521 --> 21:32.979
And I realized
I was part of this timeless love story.

21:33.058 --> 21:35.788
The truth is, sometimes I read that door
and I imagine

21:35.861 --> 21:37.522
that I have your life instead of mine.

21:37.596 --> 21:40.793
No, Molly, I am not someone you want to
live vicariously through, okay?

21:40.866 --> 21:42.663
I'm... I'm a mess.

21:42.734 --> 21:44.599
Lucas Scott didn't think so.

21:45.137 --> 21:49.096
Besides, even if you are,
no one's ever gonna write about my life.

21:57.182 --> 21:58.809
(CLEARS THROAT)

21:58.884 --> 22:02.251
- It's Marvin, right?
- Yes, sir.

22:03.322 --> 22:05.449
I suppose you heard
we had to fire Alice Day

22:05.524 --> 22:08.891
for carrying on an inappropriate
relationship with a subordinate.

22:10.662 --> 22:13.460
I suppose you know
a little something about that.

22:14.399 --> 22:16.526
- Yes, sir. I...
- It's okay, son.

22:16.835 --> 22:20.464
Apparently, half the station
knew about Alice and Rick.

22:20.539 --> 22:21.836
Rick?

22:23.975 --> 22:25.306
Evening news anchorman Rick?

22:25.377 --> 22:30.906
I know. Programming Director
sleeping with her anchor? Oh, boy.

22:30.982 --> 22:33.849
Competition's gonna love that, huh?

22:34.219 --> 22:38.747
I'm sorry, Rick, with the...
With the toupée, Rick?

22:38.924 --> 22:41.222
Listen, Marvin,
we're in a bit of a scramble here.

22:41.293 --> 22:43.989
We're gonna need all hands on deck.

22:44.129 --> 22:45.994
I watched your audition tape.

22:46.665 --> 22:51.193
It's good. You know, the Tree Hill Ravens
have their season opener coming up.

22:51.470 --> 22:53.461
How would you like to cover it?

22:55.240 --> 22:57.299
Yes, sir. Yes.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.469
- Good man.
- Thank you.

22:59.878 --> 23:02.711
McFadden, word of advice?

23:03.048 --> 23:07.144
There's opportunity here for a kid
who'll work hard and keep his nose clean.

23:08.353 --> 23:09.820
Yes, sir.

23:15.327 --> 23:17.488
What did they say?
Do they know about Carlton?

23:17.562 --> 23:20.554
- What about Carlton?
- He was giving it to Alice.

23:20.632 --> 23:21.724
What, you didn't know?

23:21.800 --> 23:23.700
They said she was sleeping with Rick.

23:23.769 --> 23:27.899
Really? Wait, wait, wait.
Anchorman Rick with the toupée?

23:27.973 --> 23:29.065
Ew!

23:29.141 --> 23:31.473
- So she was sleeping with Carlton, too?
- Oh, yeah.

23:31.543 --> 23:32.669
(SCOFFS)

23:32.744 --> 23:36.111
Hey, Mouth. They didn't say anything
about me, did they?

23:36.181 --> 23:37.842
No, why would they say...

23:38.183 --> 23:39.309
You were sleeping with her, too?

23:39.384 --> 23:41.579
Just a few mornings before work.

23:43.989 --> 23:46.549
Rick? I mean, that... That's just nasty.

23:51.963 --> 23:53.624
You ready?

23:55.066 --> 23:57.091
Okay, we're rolling.

23:58.970 --> 24:01.939
<i>Rock-a-bye my baby</i>

24:02.007 --> 24:04.805
<i>Don't be blue tonight</i>

24:04.876 --> 24:07.777
<i>Oh I'm on my way</i>

24:07.913 --> 24:10.313
Haley, did I do something to upset you?

24:12.617 --> 24:15.108
You mean besides lying and cheating?

24:15.620 --> 24:17.087
Excuse me?

24:17.689 --> 24:19.452
You told me you weren't back for Lucas.

24:19.524 --> 24:20.548
(SIGHING)

24:20.625 --> 24:22.422
- I'm not.
- That's the lying.

24:22.894 --> 24:25.829
- Haley...
- You kissed him last night. I saw you.

24:26.731 --> 24:27.891
And that's the cheating.

24:27.966 --> 24:30.491
And now I have to be the matron
of honor to a really sweet girl

24:30.569 --> 24:33.936
whose fiancé is hooking up
with his old girlfriend behind her back.

24:34.005 --> 24:37.532
So, yeah, I know we're friends, but, yeah,
Peyton, you did something to upset me.

24:37.609 --> 24:39.372
And that should upset you.

24:40.579 --> 24:42.444
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

24:43.949 --> 24:45.507
Okay, listen.

24:46.585 --> 24:50.316
You said, "No," Peyton,
and Lindsey said, "Yes."

24:51.389 --> 24:53.584
I said, "Someday."

24:54.359 --> 24:56.919
Well, Lucas fell in love in the meantime.

24:57.996 --> 25:00.760
You gotta stop trying
to take that away from him.

25:02.934 --> 25:04.094
(SIGHING)

25:04.169 --> 25:07.468
<i>Baby every time you're close to me</i>

25:07.539 --> 25:13.171
<i>Take me away to places I ain't seen</i>

25:13.245 --> 25:18.444
<i>They say you've got a hold on me</i>

25:18.984 --> 25:21.953
<i>And I Won't Disagree</i>

25:23.288 --> 25:24.277
<i>(YOU GOT YR CHERRYBOMB</i> PLAYING)

25:24.422 --> 25:28.085
But that's the thing, it's not
what he says, it's the way he says it.

25:28.159 --> 25:31.526
He honestly acts like he is above me,
which is ridiculous.

25:31.596 --> 25:34.531
He's a bartender.
He mixes drinks for a living.

25:34.599 --> 25:36.396
Like chocolate milk?

25:37.002 --> 25:38.993
Not exactly.

25:39.070 --> 25:41.595
Are you gonna kill furry
woodland creatures?

25:42.507 --> 25:45.806
I most certainly am not gonna
kill furry woodland creatures.

25:47.045 --> 25:48.410
Promise?

25:48.480 --> 25:50.414
Pinky swear, yeah.

25:50.982 --> 25:53.246
And, where was I? Oh!

25:53.318 --> 25:55.980
He should be so lucky. I am Brooke Davis.

25:56.054 --> 25:58.079
Brooke Penelope Davis.

25:58.156 --> 25:59.487
Exactly!

26:00.191 --> 26:03.922
Besides, what has he ever even said
to make me think he's worth my time?

26:03.995 --> 26:06.930
"What's underneath all the clothes,
Brooke Davis?"

26:08.433 --> 26:10.264
How old are you again?

26:10.368 --> 26:12.495
<i>Blow out that cherry bomb</i>

26:12.637 --> 26:17.904
All right. One more scoop for
the boy genius, but don't tell your mom.

26:18.410 --> 26:19.672
Come on.

26:20.078 --> 26:23.445
<i>You got to know it's on your sleeve</i>

26:25.317 --> 26:27.285
This top is really cute. Big date?

26:27.352 --> 26:29.081
Oh, just hoping to impress a guy.

26:29.154 --> 26:30.781
Well, I hope this does the trick.

26:30.855 --> 26:32.288
Fingers crossed.

26:33.124 --> 26:36.685
Millicent, you never called me back,
so I thought I'd swing by.

26:36.761 --> 26:38.820
Actually, I didn't call back on purpose.

26:38.897 --> 26:40.888
Oh, can I ask why?

26:40.966 --> 26:42.365
I don't think we're a good match.

26:42.434 --> 26:45.767
I mean, you like sports,
and I like ballet, so there's that.

26:45.837 --> 26:48.362
That's, like, the worst reason
I've ever heard.

26:48.440 --> 26:52.206
Then how about you like having sex
with your boss, and I like ballet?

26:52.677 --> 26:54.042
Brooke told me.

26:55.013 --> 26:56.503
Thank you, Brooke Davis.

26:56.581 --> 26:59.141
Look, that's completely over with,
as of last night.

26:59.217 --> 27:02.653
Well, I'm glad to hear that, Marvin,
but it's not really the point.

27:02.721 --> 27:04.712
I don't wanna date the kind of guy
who would sleep with his boss

27:04.789 --> 27:06.780
to get ahead at his job.

27:06.858 --> 27:10.487
No matter how hot or funny
or smart he is otherwise.

27:10.562 --> 27:11.824
Millicent...

27:13.598 --> 27:15.429
I'm very sorry, Marvin,

27:15.500 --> 27:19.459
but you're just not the guy
I had hoped you would be.

27:28.680 --> 27:30.910
<i>I'm Marvin McFadden, along by...</i>

27:32.250 --> 27:34.844
I'm Marvin McFadden, and with today is...

27:36.788 --> 27:38.119
You okay?

27:38.189 --> 27:40.657
I'm sorry.
This is the biggest break of my life,

27:40.725 --> 27:42.920
and I can't stop thinking
about this girl I met.

27:42.994 --> 27:44.018
Uh-huh.

27:44.095 --> 27:48.361
She thinks I'm morally bankrupt,
and the truth is, I have been lately.

27:48.433 --> 27:52.096
Come on, Mouth.
You're the most stand-up guy I know.

27:52.170 --> 27:56.630
All right, look, if it's true, turn it around.

27:59.077 --> 28:01.568
Thanks, Lucas. Where were we?

28:01.646 --> 28:04.740
You were asking me how we intend on

28:04.816 --> 28:07.216
avoiding getting our asses handed to us.

28:08.319 --> 28:10.981
I'm here with coach Lucas Scott,
whose storied buzzer-beater

28:11.056 --> 28:13.957
sealed a championship for
the Tree Hill Ravens four years ago.

28:14.025 --> 28:15.014
<i>(COME</i> HOMEPLAYING)

28:15.093 --> 28:16.390
<i>Maybe I'm wrong</i>

28:16.461 --> 28:17.951
Hi, Mom.

28:19.531 --> 28:21.522
<i>Amputate sympathy</i>

28:21.599 --> 28:24.466
So is there any way that there's, like,

28:25.370 --> 28:28.305
a cosmic loophole
that could allow you to talk to me?

28:29.407 --> 28:31.875
'Cause I could really use one of those
mother /daughter talks

28:31.943 --> 28:34.036
all the other girls are raving about.

28:39.317 --> 28:40.306
<i>How do I feel?</i>

28:40.585 --> 28:44.180
Well, Lucas

28:45.223 --> 28:47.555
has asked another girl to marry him.

28:48.793 --> 28:50.590
I know, right? Who does he think he is,

28:50.662 --> 28:54.189
asking some beautiful,

28:54.265 --> 29:00.295
brilliant successful editor over
the unemployed girl who said, "Someday"?

29:00.371 --> 29:02.498
<i>I don't mind</i>

29:05.343 --> 29:07.072
What do I do now, Mom?

29:07.912 --> 29:09.106
(SIGHS)

29:10.181 --> 29:12.172
Where do I go from here?

29:15.987 --> 29:19.514
<i>Play it by ear</i>

29:21.659 --> 29:26.255
<i>Play devil's advocate</i>

29:26.464 --> 29:27.829
Thanks, Mom.

29:27.899 --> 29:30.800
<i>Never I fear</i>

29:30.869 --> 29:32.632
(PHONE RINGING)

29:32.971 --> 29:35.098
<i>Pay for it afterwards</i>

29:35.173 --> 29:36.265
Scott residence.

29:36.341 --> 29:38.206
Hey, Carrie. It's me.

29:38.276 --> 29:40.642
Listen, I have been making
some great progress with Mia,

29:40.712 --> 29:42.270
and I was hoping to put in
a few more hours

29:42.347 --> 29:45.578
but I wasn't sure if Jamie and Nathan
were waiting on me for dinner.

29:46.551 --> 29:49.816
They're not home right now,
but I'll handle dinner if they show up.

29:49.888 --> 29:50.912
<i>HALEY: Really? That would be great.</i>

29:50.989 --> 29:53.287
Thank you. You're a lifesaver.

29:53.525 --> 29:54.856
Just happy to help.

29:54.926 --> 29:58.623
<i>Nobody ever says goodbye</i>

29:59.097 --> 30:01.122
Boys, dinner's ready.

30:04.469 --> 30:06.664
<i>Come home</i>

30:10.942 --> 30:14.002
Let me see that. Oh, it's genius.

30:14.078 --> 30:15.545
It's a work of art.

30:16.047 --> 30:18.379
A work of art. Look, Mama.

30:19.384 --> 30:21.318
I mean, Nanny Carrie.

30:31.996 --> 30:36.296
Hi, I've been thinking about
what you said earlier, and I get it.

30:36.367 --> 30:39.234
I wouldn't want to date you if
you were sleeping with your boss, either.

30:39.304 --> 30:40.498
Brooke?

30:41.072 --> 30:42.539
No, Victoria.

30:42.807 --> 30:43.831
Ew!

30:43.908 --> 30:47.139
I would totally date you
if you were sleeping with Brooke.

30:48.313 --> 30:52.409
Millicent, wait, I'm not that guy.

30:52.784 --> 30:55.617
At least that's not the guy
I've been in the past.

30:56.287 --> 31:00.018
Would you give me just one chance
to prove that to you, please?

31:01.092 --> 31:02.821
I promise it's not a date.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.502
Go home.

31:20.612 --> 31:24.412
But first, we toast your engagement.

31:24.883 --> 31:26.908
- Oh.
- Ha, ha.

31:29.153 --> 31:30.780
You know, I'm nervous.

31:32.423 --> 31:34.186
Oh, don't be nervous.

31:34.259 --> 31:37.490
Them chumps at La Salle,
they won't even know what hit 'em.

31:38.596 --> 31:40.689
Yeah, I'm not talking about the game.

31:40.765 --> 31:42.255
I know.

31:42.700 --> 31:46.158
Look, I was nervous my first time, too.

31:46.237 --> 31:51.231
Just remember. It's a beautiful expression
of love between a man and a woman.

31:51.309 --> 31:53.402
(BOTH LAUGHING)

31:54.212 --> 31:56.908
- Very funny.
- Luke, you're a man.

31:57.181 --> 31:59.843
I'd be worried if you said
you wasn't nervous.

32:01.586 --> 32:05.818
So, here's to my friend Lucas Scott,

32:06.190 --> 32:11.924
who don't need to be nervous because
he always, without fail, follows his heart.

32:12.530 --> 32:13.622
Huh.

32:14.465 --> 32:15.625
Cheers.

32:16.901 --> 32:17.890
Hmm!

32:18.469 --> 32:19.663
God.

32:22.040 --> 32:23.371
<i>(PEOPLE CHEERING)</i>

32:24.208 --> 32:26.403
- All right, how about just one more?
- Yeah.

32:32.450 --> 32:33.940
Where are we?

32:34.018 --> 32:37.545
I know it doesn't look like much,
but this is my favorite room in the world.

32:37.622 --> 32:42.582
With our satellite, I can find almost
any sporting event anywhere, anytime.

32:42.660 --> 32:45.493
That's great, but why?
I mean, why sports?

32:45.563 --> 32:49.897
I guess, when I watch a game, it reminds
me we all have greatness inside of us.

32:51.436 --> 32:54.667
You know, on any given day,
an underdog can rise up.

32:55.340 --> 32:56.739
Gives me hope.

32:56.874 --> 32:58.774
<i>(PITTERPA</i> TPLAYING)

33:01.913 --> 33:03.380
Here we go.

33:03.448 --> 33:06.542
- What's this?
- The Moscow Ballet.

33:06.617 --> 33:08.414
I hear they're pretty good.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.716
<i>Turned this bedroom upside down tonight</i>

33:10.788 --> 33:12.517
I don't understand.

33:13.391 --> 33:16.417
Well, I was hoping you would tell me
why you love ballet.

33:16.494 --> 33:18.724
'Cause I think you're really great, Millicent,

33:18.796 --> 33:20.991
and I'd love to know more about you.

33:21.065 --> 33:24.262
<i>Pain takes my heart's place</i>

33:25.069 --> 33:27.299
I'm sorry I called you "Mama."

33:28.239 --> 33:29.570
It's okay.

33:31.009 --> 33:32.738
You wanna hear a secret?

33:34.145 --> 33:35.305
(GRUNTING)

33:37.015 --> 33:38.039
<i>Pitter pat, the angel on my shoulder</i>

33:38.116 --> 33:40.676
Sometimes I pretend you're my kid.

33:41.686 --> 33:44.519
<i>Is haunting me tonight</i>

33:44.589 --> 33:48.320
<i>Tick tock, the clock is getting louder</i>

33:48.393 --> 33:51.487
<i>Ready for me to decide</i>

33:54.232 --> 33:58.669
<i>Pain takes my heart's place</i>

34:00.638 --> 34:05.803
<i>But your sweet sweet love</i>
<i>Oh I can taste it</i>

34:07.045 --> 34:10.536
<i>But still can't face it</i>

34:12.016 --> 34:15.975
<i>Pitter pat, the angel on my shoulder</i>

34:16.454 --> 34:19.252
<i>Is haunting me tonight</i>

34:20.224 --> 34:23.318
- You're so good with him.
- No, he's good with me.

34:23.494 --> 34:24.483
(SIGHING)

34:25.228 --> 34:27.163
What? What's so funny?

34:27.231 --> 34:32.134
Nothing, just, you've had paint
on your face for the past two hours.

34:32.203 --> 34:34.068
Why didn't you tell me? Where?

34:34.138 --> 34:35.435
Here.

34:37.909 --> 34:39.672
Wait a minute. Close your eyes.

34:39.744 --> 34:42.645
You actually managed to get paint
on your eyelids.

34:42.713 --> 34:45.079
- Okay.
- Hold on. I'll get it.

34:48.052 --> 34:52.318
<i>The sun is coming down on me</i>

34:52.989 --> 34:56.585
<i>Could fate be so unkind?</i>

34:56.661 --> 34:58.253
Nanny Carrie!

35:00.364 --> 35:04.824
<i>Pain takes my heart's place</i>

35:06.904 --> 35:11.739
<i>The love we made remains</i>

35:23.688 --> 35:25.280
PEYTON: Hey.

35:26.390 --> 35:28.290
Do you think maybe Whitey
will let you out of practice early

35:28.359 --> 35:29.519
so we can catch a movie?

35:30.294 --> 35:31.522
(CHUCKLES)

35:32.530 --> 35:34.327
What are you doing, Peyton?

35:34.398 --> 35:38.732
I'm just pretending for a second that
we're still 17 and nothing's changed.

35:39.937 --> 35:44.340
Would you believe I actually met a girl
who lives vicariously through us?

35:44.642 --> 35:46.473
At least the us in the book?

35:47.612 --> 35:48.977
Sure, I do.

35:50.748 --> 35:56.448
It was a great story to be a part of,
but it also took place a long time ago.

35:57.688 --> 36:02.182
I know.
I didn't come here to rehash the past.

36:04.028 --> 36:08.089
I was reminded today in a roundabout way

36:08.966 --> 36:12.458
that the most perfect act of love
is sacrifice.

36:13.905 --> 36:15.964
That's what Keith did for Karen.

36:17.408 --> 36:21.640
Burying his feelings for her for all those
years so he could be a good friend.

36:28.419 --> 36:29.750
(PEYTON SIGHING)

36:33.324 --> 36:35.315
I love you, Lucas.

36:38.196 --> 36:41.359
And I think I have
since the first moment we locked eyes.

36:43.067 --> 36:45.194
And it is gonna suck!

36:46.938 --> 36:50.533
But if what you want is for me to let go,

36:51.842 --> 36:53.605
then I'm gonna do it.

36:57.081 --> 36:58.844
Be happy, Luke.

37:00.418 --> 37:02.079
I want that with all my heart.

37:28.346 --> 37:30.007
<i>(ASHES AND</i> WINEPLAYING)

37:30.081 --> 37:33.346
<i>PEYTON: Dear Molly,</i>
<i>this is gonna sound a little strange.</i>

37:33.417 --> 37:36.875
<i>But I'd like you to paint over</i>
<i>my old closet door.</i>

37:37.355 --> 37:40.916
<i>The thing is, there is never a time</i>
<i>when you'll be more honest,</i>

37:40.992 --> 37:43.256
<i>when your convictions will be stronger</i>

37:43.327 --> 37:47.161
<i>or when your motives will be more pure</i>
<i>than they are right now.</i>

37:47.331 --> 37:50.562
<i>Which means you should chase</i>
<i>whatever it is that excites you.</i>

37:50.635 --> 37:55.072
They have such perfect lines
and grace and power.

37:55.706 --> 37:59.665
If I closed my eyes, you could totally
be talking about sports right now.

38:00.678 --> 38:02.373
Maybe you should try it.

38:02.513 --> 38:03.741
Ballet?

38:03.814 --> 38:05.372
Closing your eyes.

38:05.449 --> 38:06.438
<i>All the same</i>

38:09.720 --> 38:12.484
<i>I don't want mudslinging games</i>

38:12.556 --> 38:15.218
<i>PEYTON: Be confident and take risks.</i>

38:15.393 --> 38:17.088
<i>It's just a shame</i>

38:17.161 --> 38:20.653
<i>And paint over my words</i>
<i>so you can start writing your own.</i>

38:20.731 --> 38:22.824
<i>To let you walk away</i>

38:23.868 --> 38:27.531
<i>Is there a chance?</i>

38:27.605 --> 38:31.507
<i>A fragment of light</i>
<i>at the end of the tunnel?</i>

38:31.575 --> 38:33.805
I assume you're not carjacking me.

38:34.178 --> 38:36.976
You said you wanted to know
what was under the clothes.

38:37.048 --> 38:39.016
I was being existential.

38:40.117 --> 38:43.245
I was being literal and serious.

38:47.925 --> 38:50.155
<i>Or are we ashes and wine?</i>

38:50.227 --> 38:52.559
You make two fantastic points.

38:55.866 --> 38:57.333
I should be getting home.

38:57.401 --> 38:59.801
What? You're turning down naked me?

38:59.870 --> 39:02.338
Nobody turns down naked me.

39:02.907 --> 39:05.102
Relax. It was a joke.

39:05.476 --> 39:08.138
- You win.
- Really?

39:08.212 --> 39:11.613
Absolutely. Let's have sex, Brooke Davis.

39:11.682 --> 39:13.673
Your place or mine?

39:13.751 --> 39:15.048
As if.

39:17.722 --> 39:22.785
<i>I'm ill with the thought of your kiss</i>

39:24.462 --> 39:26.726
You haven't earned that, bartender boy.

39:26.797 --> 39:29.960
<i>Coffee laced intoxicating on her lips</i>

39:30.034 --> 39:31.501
Sleep tight.

39:32.370 --> 39:34.838
<i>PEYTON: My story may have inspired you,</i>

39:34.905 --> 39:39.365
<i>but I'm certain your story will inspire</i>
<i>the next girl to live in our room.</i>

39:39.643 --> 39:41.110
Attagirl.

39:41.746 --> 39:44.374
<i>Not allowed to wear your freedom down</i>

39:44.448 --> 39:47.679
- Hi.
- Hey. You're home late.

39:47.752 --> 39:51.415
Yeah, sorry.
Mia's album is sounding awesome.

39:51.522 --> 39:56.016
Great. Just wish you were home more.

39:57.495 --> 39:59.019
Thanks. Me, too.

40:00.698 --> 40:01.995
Yeah.

40:02.833 --> 40:04.824
God, it's been a long day.

40:05.469 --> 40:08.233
Snapped at Lucas,
basically called Peyton a whore.

40:08.305 --> 40:09.932
I feel pretty lousy about it.

40:10.007 --> 40:12.498
Are you gonna tell Lindsey about the kiss?

40:13.778 --> 40:17.680
I don't know. I'm starting to think
some things are better left secrets.

40:18.282 --> 40:21.308
Hi. I'm going to bed now, okay?

40:22.019 --> 40:23.577
Yeah, great. We're fine here.

40:23.654 --> 40:25.918
Just let me know if you need me.

40:30.327 --> 40:32.591
<i>That is what you need</i>

40:33.664 --> 40:37.464
<i>PEYTON: I want you to know, you don't</i>
<i>need somebody to write about you</i>

40:37.535 --> 40:40.265
<i>in order for your life to mean something.</i>

40:40.337 --> 40:43.704
<i>You can write about yourself,</i>
<i>make your own destiny.</i>

40:45.643 --> 40:50.171
<i>Then, years from now, the next girl will</i>
<i>keep what you write on that door</i>

40:50.247 --> 40:53.944
<i>long enough to remind you</i>
<i>of how inspired your life is.</i>

40:55.920 --> 40:58.980
<i>And you can tell that girl</i>
<i>to paint over the door</i>

40:59.056 --> 41:01.490
<i>because you realize the words you wrote,</i>

41:01.592 --> 41:07.121
<i>the friends you had, the urgency you felt</i>
<i>will always be there underneath the paint.</i>

41:07.531 --> 41:09.658
Let's get married right away.

41:11.969 --> 41:14.767
<i>PEYTON: The love you professed</i>
<i>will always be there.</i>

41:14.839 --> 41:19.139
<i>The spark of something</i>
<i>undeniable, a seed of hope.</i>

41:19.210 --> 41:24.204
<i>The truth, for better or for worse,</i>
<i>burning fiercely, just below the surface.</i>

41:25.149 --> 41:29.483
<i>Or are we ashes and wine?</i>

41:30.855 --> 41:32.652
<i>Love, Peyton.</i>

